trans-unit.source: Encapsulates basic validation rules that indicate whether a piece of custom data is considered personalizable in either <see cref="F:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User" /> or <see cref="F:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared" /> scope.

A <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> instance is a collection of <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry> objects, which consist of a personalization scope and an object value.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> instância é uma coleção de <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationEntry> objetos, que consistem em um escopo de personalização e um valor de objeto.

trans-unit.source: These entries are assigned a key in the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> object.
trans-unit.target: Essas entradas são atribuídas a uma chave de <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> objeto.

trans-unit.source: A good practice is to add all properties to the dictionary using the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> method, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: Uma prática recomendada é adicionar todas as propriedades para o dicionário usando o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> método, independentemente do escopo da página.

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework saves the information in the appropriate way; for example, shared data is saved when the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope.
trans-unit.target: O .NET Framework salva as informações da maneira apropriada; Por exemplo, os dados compartilhados é salvo quando a página estiver no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo.

trans-unit.source: However, shared properties are not saved when a Web Parts value is being saved, the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope, and the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added with the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, as propriedades compartilhadas não são salvas quando um valor de Web Parts está sendo salvo, a página está no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo e o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controle foi adicionado com a página no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary" /> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary" /> class.

trans-unit.target: Este construtor inicializa um dicionário vazio.

trans-unit.source: The dictionary will treat key values as case-insensitive.
trans-unit.target: O dicionário tratará os valores de chave como maiusculas e minúsculas.

trans-unit.source: The estimated number of entries to be stored in the dictionary.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary" /> class using the provided parameter.
This constructor initializes an empty dictionary based on the estimated number of entries to be stored in the dictionary.
trans-unit.target: Este construtor inicializa um dicionário vazio com base no número estimado de entradas a ser armazenado no dicionário.

trans-unit.source: The dictionary will treat key values as case-insensitive.
trans-unit.target: O dicionário tratará os valores de chave como maiusculas e minúsculas.

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier for a piece of state information.
A piece of state information to be added to the personalization dictionary.
This value can be <see langword="null" />.
Adds personalization entries to the personalization dictionary.
You can call this method, place various pieces of custom state information into the state object, and specify the scope associated with the state value.
trans-unit.target: Você pode chamar esse método, colocar várias partes das informações de estado personalizado para o objeto de estado e especificar o escopo associado com o valor de estado.

trans-unit.source: When a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> control is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope, you can add name and state information that is associated with either <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope.
trans-unit.target: Quando um <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPartManager> controle está no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo, você pode adicionar informações de nome e o estado associado um <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo ou <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo.

trans-unit.source: In <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope, you can add name and state information associated only with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope.
trans-unit.target: Em <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo, você pode adicionar informações de nome e o estado associadas apenas <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo.

trans-unit.source: It is a good practice, however, to add all properties to the dictionary using <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> including properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> or <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope, regardless of the scope of the page.
trans-unit.target: É uma prática recomendada, no entanto, para adicionar todas as propriedades para o dicionário usando <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.IPersonalizable.Save%2A> incluindo propriedades com <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> ou <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo, independentemente do escopo da página.

trans-unit.source: The .NET Framework only saves the properties with <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope when appropriate.
trans-unit.target: O .NET Framework salva apenas as propriedades com <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo quando apropriado.

trans-unit.source: In other words, shared properties are not saved when a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control that was initially added in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope.
trans-unit.target: Em outras palavras, compartilhado propriedades não são salvas quando um <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controle que foi inicialmente adicionada em <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo for salvo enquanto a página estiver no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo.

trans-unit.source: In an opposite scenario, if a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> control was added to the page in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> scope, and the control is later saved while the page is in <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> scope, custom shared property values are saved (along with custom user-scoped properties).
trans-unit.target: Em um cenário oposto, se um <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.WebPart> controle foi adicionado para a página <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.User> escopo e o controle for salvo enquanto a página estiver no <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationScope.Shared> escopo, os valores de propriedade compartilhada personalizada são salvos (junto com propriedades personalizadas no escopo do usuário).

trans-unit.source: For details on personalization data and how shared and user-scoped properties are affected by the personalization scope of the page, see the [Web Parts Personalization Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7dc34f74-52aa-4082-b98d-2bcf9e07e320) topic.
trans-unit.target: Para obter detalhes sobre os dados de personalização e propriedades como compartilhadas e no escopo do usuário são afetadas pelo escopo de personalização da página, consulte o [Web Parts Personalization Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7dc34f74-52aa-4082-b98d-2bcf9e07e320) tópico.

trans-unit.target: Se `key` ainda não existir, então `key` (e seu valor associado) são adicionados ao dicionário.

trans-unit.source: Note that you can add a null value to the dictionary, and the indexer can also be used to update the personalization value.
trans-unit.target: Observe que você pode adicionar um valor nulo ao dicionário, e o indexador também pode ser usado para atualizar o valor de personalização.

trans-unit.source: If the checks are successful, the method calls the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> class's own <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Add%2A> method, passing to it the `key` and `value` parameters.
trans-unit.target: Se as verificações forem bem-sucedidas, o método chama o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> da classe <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Add%2A> método, passando a ele o `key` e `value` parâmetros.

trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Remove%2A> método verifica se `key` é um <xref:System.String> objeto, e se assim, ele chama o <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary> da classe <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.WebParts.PersonalizationDictionary.Remove%2A> método, passando `key` a ele.
